Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2015 16:11:40 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 112/132] MIPS: Select USB_ARCH_HAS_XHCI for CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC

This allows us to select the xhci driver with PCI disabled.  A
supported configuration on OCTEON.

Signed-off-by: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
Signed-off-by: Abhishek Paliwal <abhishek.paliwal@aricent.com>
[Original patch taken from OCTEON-SDK 3.1.1-544.]
Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/mips/Kconfig b/arch/mips/Kconfig
index a8bde39..4643bf1 100644
--- a/arch/mips/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/Kconfig
@@ -840,6 +840,7 @@ config CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC
 	select MIPS_NR_CPU_NR_MAP_1024
 	select SYS_SUPPORTS_NUMA
 	select HANDLE_DOMAIN_IRQ
+	select USB_ARCH_HAS_XHCI
 	select BUILTIN_DTB
 	select MTD_COMPLEX_MAPPINGS
 	help
